# Architecture — Clean Architecture, Feature-First

```
lib/
├── main.dart / app.dart / initialization.dart
├── core/            # DI, config, database (drift), network, routing, state, theme, widgets
└── features/<feature>/
    ├── data/         # sources, repository implementations, services
    ├── domain/       # entities, models, repository interfaces, preference stores
    └── presentation/ # bloc/, pages/ (@RoutePage), widgets/
```

Shared UI/utilities live in `lib/core/`, imported via
`package:hondana/core/core.dart`. No `packages/` monorepo, no Firebase.

## Layer boundaries

- **Pages hold no business logic.** They compose a Bloc + UI. Orchestration
  (downloads, app-lock, library updates, source resolution) lives in
  `data/`/`domain/` services and is driven through the Bloc.
- **No network or database access in presentation.** Sources/repositories fetch
  and expose `Stream`s / result types; Blocs call them; pages render state.
- **Keep drift types out of `domain/`.** Map rows to domain entities at the data
  boundary (`Manga.fromData(...)`).
- **Repositories** expose intent-level methods and `Stream`s; concrete sources /
  drift live behind them.

## Features

`browse` (sources / extensions / global search), `library`, `manga` (details),
`reader`, `downloads`, `history`, `updates`, `more` (settings), `main` (shell).

## Sources & extensions

Mihon's source system is ported under `features/browse/`: `domain/source/`
(the `Source` abstraction + `SManga`/`SChapter`/`MangasPage`/`Filter` models),
`data/source/` (`HttpSource` base, `LocalSource`, and site families). Resolve by
id via `SourceManager`.
